      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:5:2:159:11",
      "relations": null,
      "text": [
        " نَهَى رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) أَنْ يُؤْكَلُ مَا تَحْمِلُ النَّمْلَةُ بِفِيهَا وَ قَوَائِمِهَا ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hammad, from Al Halby, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> forbade from eating what the ant carried with its mouth and its legs’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "11. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hammad from al-Halabiy who has said the following: “Abu ‘ Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that the Messenger of Allah prohibited eating of what ants carry in their mouth or with their legs.” "
        ]
      }
    }
